Package com.googlecode.aluminumproject.converters.common

A number of common converters.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayToIterableConverter
    Converts arrays (of any type, including primitives) to iterables.
    NumberToNumberConverter
    Converts from one kind of number to another.
    ObjectToStringConverter
    Converts objects to strings by using the toString method.
    StringToBooleanConverter
    Converts strings into booleans by using the parseBoolean method.
    StringToEnumConverter
    Converts the name of an to enum into an enum constant.
    StringToNumberConverter
    Converts strings to bytes, shorts, integers, longs, floats, doubles, big integers, and big decimals using the various valueOf-methods and, for big integers and big decimals, constructors.
